		{
			"id": 1,
			"parent": 3,
			"text": "All-trans retinoic acid ( RA ) is an important morphogen in vertebrate development , a normal constituent in human adult blood",
			"relation": "BACKGROUND",
			"tag": "Background"
		},
		{
			"id": 2,
			"parent": 1,
			"text": "and is also involved in the control of cell growth and differentiation in acute promyelocytic leukemia . <S>",
			"relation": "ADDITION",
			"tag": "Background"
		},
		{
			"id": 3,
			"parent": 0,
			"text": "We have examined the effects of RA on normal hematopoiesis",
			"relation": "ROOT",
			"tag": "Hypothesis-Objective"
		},
		{
			"id": 4,
			"parent": 3,
			"text": "by using early hematopoietic progenitor cells ( HPC ) stringently purified from adult peripheral blood . <S>",
			"relation": "MANNER-MEANS",
			"tag": "Verification-Method"
		},
		{
			"id": 5,
			"parent": 3,
			"text": "In clonogenetic fetal calf serum-supplemented ( FCS+ ) or -nonsupplemented ( FCS- ) culture treated with saturating levels of interleukin-3 ( IL-3 ) granulocyte-macrophage colony-stimulating factor ( GM-CSF ) and erythropoietin ( Ep ) ( combined with c-kit ligand in FCS(-)-culture conditions ) , RA induces a dramatic dose-dependent shift from erythroid to granulomonocytic colony formation ,",
			"relation": "VERIFICATION",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 6,
			"parent": 5,
			"text": "the latter colonies being essentially represented by granulocytic clones . <S>",
			"relation": "TEMPORAL",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 7,
			"parent": 5,
			"text": "This shift is apparently not caused by a recruitment phenomenon ,",
			"relation": "ELABORATION",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 8,
			"parent": 7,
			"text": "because in FCS+ culture , the total number of colonies is not significantly modified by RA addition . <S>",
			"relation": "CAUSE-RESULT",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 9,
			"parent": 5,
			"text": "In FCS- liquid-suspension culture supplemented with saturating Ep level and low-dose IL-3/GM-CSF , adult HPC undergo unilineage erythropoietic differentiation :",
			"relation": "ADDITION",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 10,
			"parent": 9,
			"text": "Here again , treatment with high-dose RA induces a shift from the erythroid to granulocytic differentiation pathway . <S>",
			"relation": "ADDITION",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 11,
			"parent": 5,
			"text": "Studies on RA time-response or pulse treatment in semisolid or liquid culture show",
			"relation": "ADDITION",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 12,
			"parent": 11,
			"text": "that early RA addition is most effective ,",
			"relation": "ATTRIBUTION",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 13,
			"parent": 12,
			"text": "thus indicating",
			"relation": "CAUSE-RESULT",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 14,
			"parent": 13,
			"text": "that early but not late HPC are sensitive to its action . <S>",
			"relation": "ATTRIBUTION",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 15,
			"parent": 3,
			"text": "We then analyzed the expression of the master GATA1 gene , which encodes a finger transcription factor required for normal erythroid development ;",
			"relation": "ADDITION",
			"tag": "Hypothesis-Objective"
		},
		{
			"id": 16,
			"parent": 15,
			"text": "addition of RA to HPC stimulated into unilineage erythropoietic differentiation in liquid culture caused a virtually complete inhibition of GATA1 mRNA induction . <S>",
			"relation": "VERIFICATION",
			"tag": "Verification-Result"
		},
		{
			"id": 17,
			"parent": 3,
			"text": "These results indicate",
			"relation": "CONCLUSION",
			"tag": "Conclusion"
		},
		{
			"id": 18,
			"parent": 17,
			"text": "that RA directly inhibits the erythroid differentiation program at the level of early adult HPC ,",
			"relation": "ATTRIBUTION",
			"tag": "Conclusion"
		},
		{
			"id": 19,
			"parent": 18,
			"text": "and may lead to a shift from the erythroid to granulocytic differentiation pathway . <S>",
			"relation": "ADDITION",
			"tag": "Conclusion"
		},
		{
			"id": 20,
			"parent": 17,
			"text": "This phenomenon is correlated with inhibition of GATA1 induction in the early stages of erythropoietic differentiation . <S>",
			"relation": "ELABORATION",
			"tag": "Conclusion"
		}
	]
}